Multiple Means for Internet Access: Available with wired network access, high speed LTE CAT4 and Wi-Fi connection. One LAN port, one WAN/LAN switchable port and Wi-Fi access. Support multiple WAN access methods, including PPP、PPPoE、DHCP ; Supports WIFI, Compatible with 802.11b/g/n, AP, Client and WDS modes The IR300 is a compact M2M LTE router integrating 4G LTE, Wi-Fi, and VPN technologies.

Strong Security Protection: Supports VPN, firewall and user authorization management. High Reliability & Efficient Remote management: Watchdog and multi-layer link detection mechanisms ,automatic redial and recovery; Dual-SIM failover; VRRP mechanism for backup; Failover between wired, cellular LTE networks and Wi-Fi. manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: How to use the router with SIM card ? Notice: If you are not sure which model you want to order, if you were encounterd trouble using the device, please tell us. We will try our best to solve the problem for you 1. Insert the SIM card into the slot 1 and attach 4G antennas to the Main and AUX connectors; then power cycle the device. To replace or insert SIM Card, the device must be powered off to avoid data loss or equipment damage. 2. Connect the LAN2 port with your PC. 3. Fill in the IP of the router on the browser (you could find the IP on the label of router). IP: 192.168.2.1 User name/password: adm/123456 4. Go to 'network >>Cellular', select 'profile 1' under the network provider, fill in the SIM card information in the Profiles table down below: APN, User Name, Password, (User Name and Password are not mandatory), hit 'ok' and 'Apply'. Notice: Please make sure the APN is correct. If you are not sure, please confirmwith ISP or search it on Google. Below are the example of APN information AT &T's APN: broadband Verizon’s APN: vzwinternet Some sim cards can get a static IP and require some specific APNs, please confirm with your Carrier. 5. Check the network status, 'Status >> Network connection'

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars works great in a remote location for internet access and wifi cameras
reviews.reviewText: Setup was fairly quick and easy. Finding a good cellular plan that worked good in my area at an affordable price was the hardest part. Once I found a reliable and affordable cellular provider it worked really well. I am able to make changes by the remote web management from the manufacturer web page and view online status. I am also able to text the sim card number and get online status and force a reboot if needed. Still working on remote access to a raspberry pi but have not had the time for it yet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works Great but Requires User to be Slightly Tech Savvy
reviews.reviewText: Modem appears well made and once configured, runs great. It is not as user friendly to setup like a sierra wireless, mofi, or peplink modem but if you know how to set your own APN and understand how to configure WAN/LAN settings, you will do just fine with this unit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a great industrial cellular router
reviews.reviewText: Once the configuration is navigated, replicating the process is easy.The only confusing part is security protocols for a non-professional.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You should have experience setting up a router
reviews.reviewText: There was small amount of difficulty setting it up but the tech-support from inhand is excellent. There’s also a 60 page online manual that can be very helpful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars The default log in is wrong
reviews.reviewText: The manual and everything online states the log in is adm for the username and the password is 123456 That is not the case here. I have reset this thing several times by unplugging it, plug it in and within 5 seconds hold the reset switch until the status led lights, then let go, wait for it to go off and hold the reset again until the led starts to flash, then let go. I wait for it to reboot, go the 192.168.2.1 and put in adm and 123456 and I am told the login failed check username and password. It's a paperweight I waisted $180 on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Since I got this product my streaming business have improved. Signals are pretty steady and you can see the improvement in low signal area

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars s much as I want to like the product... Sends secure data in the CLEAR
reviews.reviewText: We're looking for a cellular backhaul solution for temporary security cameras for real estate. Using a cell connection requires a dynamic DNS service. The device offers one BUT it sends sensitive data in the CLEAR via an http NOT https connection and dynamic DNS services do not like that. When I noticed the issue, I contacted customer service to see if there was a patch to fix. I'm still waiting for a call back a week later. Returned

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars 100Mbps ports, limited config options
reviews.reviewText: This thing has only 100MBps ethernet ports, supported wifi is pretty outdated and the configuration UI is cryptic, lacking and buggy (for example, you can't configure routes freely, this thing will force gateway configuration on WAN port). However, it does support VPN and other features, making it a decent backup solution.

This device is a piece of junk.The instructions are inaccurate which makes dealing with it pretty annoying.At the end of the day this is the problem:With SIM card inserted and factory reset performed, the device will connect via Cellular network with DEFAULT SETTINGSThe moment you CHANGE ANY SETTING OTHER THAN THE ADMIN PASSWORD - the device STOPS ROUTING TRAFFIC.Being that this was purchased for its failover aspect and simply enabling failover causes the device to stop routing, this item is being returned.
